Package view

Class StudentUi

  • java.lang.Object
    • view.Ui
      • view.StudentUi
  • public class StudentUi
extends Ui
    This class is responsible for the logic of getting input and output from the user for tasks related to the Student panel.

      • getIndexOfCourseToChange

        public int getIndexOfCourseToChange​(java.util.ArrayList<Course> courses)
        Displays all the registered courses and get the user to input which course he/she would like to change. This method will always get the user to input a valid integer from 1 to size of courses and return an integer from 0 to size of courses - 1.
        Parameters:
        courses - An ArrayList of Course containing all the registered courses for a student.
        Returns:
        The integer representing the index of courses for which the student has chosen.

      • getIndexOfIndexNumberToChange

        public int getIndexOfIndexNumberToChange​(java.util.ArrayList<IndexNumber> indexNumbers)
        Displays all the index numbers for a particular course for which the student wants to change the index number for. The method will always get the user to input a valid integer from 1 to size of indexNumbers and return an integer from 0 to size of indexNumbers - 1.
        Parameters:
        indexNumbers - An ArrayList of IndexNumber that is associated with the course that the student wants to change index number for.
        Returns:
        The integer representing the index of the indexNumbers for which the student has chosen.

      • getIndexOfCourseToDrop

        public int getIndexOfCourseToDrop​(java.util.ArrayList<Course> courses,
                                  boolean dropRegistered)
        Displays all the courses registered or all the courses in wait list and ask the user to input which course he/she would like to drop.
        Parameters:
        courses - An ArrayList of Course.
        dropRegistered - true if the user wants to drop a registered course; false if the user wants to drop a course on the wait list.
        Returns:
        The integer representing the index of the courses for which the user wants to drop.

      • getIndexOfCourseToRegister

        public int getIndexOfCourseToRegister​(java.util.ArrayList<Course> courses)
        Displays all the courses and get the user to choose which course they would like to add. The method will always get the user to input a valid integer from 1 to size of courses and return an integer from 0 to size of courses - 1.
        Parameters:
        courses - An ArrayList of Course.
        Returns:
        The integer representing the index of courses that the user wants to register for.

      • getIndexOfIndexNumberToRegister

        public int getIndexOfIndexNumberToRegister​(java.util.ArrayList<IndexNumber> indexNumbers)
        Displays all the index numbers associated with a particular course and get the user to input which index number he/she wants to register for. The method will always get the user to input a valid integer from 1 to size of indexNumbers and return an integer from 0 to size of indexNumbers - 1.
        Parameters:
        indexNumbers - An ArrayList of IndexNumber that are associated with the course that the user wants to register for.
        Returns:
        The integer representing the index of the indexNumbers for which the user wants to register for.

      • confirmSwapWithPeer

        public boolean confirmSwapWithPeer​(Student student,
                                   Student peer,
                                   Course courseToBeSwapped)
        Get confirmation from the user that he/she is going to swap the index number for a particular course with another peer.
        Parameters:
        student - The Student who wants to swap an index number with the peer.
        peer - The peer who is going to swap an index number with the student.
        courseToBeSwapped - The Course for which the student and peer is going to be swapped.
        Returns:
        true if the user confirms the swap; false if the user do not confirm the swap.
